WEBVTT

00:01.668 --> 00:02.692
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

00:02.870 --> 00:03.894
Yo.

00:04.571 --> 00:08.064
Uh, these are the indecent-exposure files.
Where do you want them?

00:08.242 --> 00:11.007
Sex offenses on the sofa.

00:12.980 --> 00:18.111
FLORENCE: I can't believe that
they make you go through every case.

00:18.785 --> 00:20.981
It's the year-end report.
I don't mind really.

00:21.154 --> 00:23.248
Gives me a chance
to review my performance...

00:23.423 --> 00:25.414
...reflect on old memories.

00:25.592 --> 00:28.823
Remember that carnival geek
married his dog?

00:29.563 --> 00:32.658
Yeah. It's over.
I ran into her the other day.

00:32.833 --> 00:35.996
- What happened?
- I ran into her the other day.

00:37.304 --> 00:38.965
[SIGHS]

00:39.473 --> 00:43.205
I feel funny though. Working here while
the gang's out there with another judge.

00:43.377 --> 00:45.709
You're not missing anything good.
I saw the docket.

00:45.879 --> 00:47.643
It looks like a fairly routine night.

00:53.053 --> 00:55.750
Sir, I'm gonna take Mac down to jail now.

00:56.290 --> 01:00.284
- What?
- I got busted for contempt of court.

01:03.230 --> 01:07.224
When you go through the strip search,
ask for Gentle Ben.

01:09.000 --> 01:15.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:53.313 --> 01:54.542
What happened?

01:54.715 --> 01:56.683
Mac just walked over
with the docket, sir.

01:56.850 --> 01:59.319
Next thing I know,
Judge Hirsch told me to take him.

01:59.486 --> 02:02.046
- For what reason?
- He said my sweater...

02:02.222 --> 02:04.554
...was a mockery of justice.

02:06.259 --> 02:08.023
Well, it's not that bad.

02:10.163 --> 02:12.757
Oh, come on, Mac.
Obviously, the man is joking with you.

02:12.933 --> 02:14.765
No, no, sir. This is serious.

02:14.935 --> 02:16.562
Judge Hirsch is crazy.

02:16.737 --> 02:19.638
Mac, don't go jumping
to drastic conclusions.

02:19.806 --> 02:23.606
You know we each have
our own unique style.

02:26.046 --> 02:29.277
Judge Hirsch just ordered a defendant
to clean the Holland Tunnel.

02:29.449 --> 02:32.384
- So?
- With his tongue.

02:33.487 --> 02:35.956
I think I will have a little peek.

02:37.424 --> 02:40.359
Come on. I can get you down to holding
before they serve dinner.

02:40.527 --> 02:41.892
What are we having?

02:42.062 --> 02:44.759
There was talk of Spam balls.

02:53.240 --> 02:54.503
Sir?

02:54.675 --> 02:56.643
Quiet. I'm almost finished.

02:59.479 --> 03:02.779
Well, ha-ha-ha, what do you think?

03:05.085 --> 03:07.213
That's superb. Ha, ha.

03:09.456 --> 03:10.651
Phil...

03:10.824 --> 03:12.622
...what's going on?

03:12.793 --> 03:16.559
That is not a well man.

03:17.364 --> 03:21.494
He just put out a bench warrant
for the Rockettes.

03:22.035 --> 03:23.196
What charge?

03:23.370 --> 03:25.600
Espionage.

03:26.339 --> 03:32.176
He's convinced the Soviets have implanted
tiny transmitters in their legs.

03:32.345 --> 03:38.307
He says, “This explains the high incidence
of varicose veins after they retire.“

03:39.619 --> 03:44.056
Personally.
I like a little texture to my women.

03:45.592 --> 03:49.222
- Uh, excuse me, sir, about my client...
- Oh, right. Hang him.

03:50.597 --> 03:52.827
He stole an Eskimo Pie, sir.

03:53.467 --> 03:55.401
Nap time.

03:58.605 --> 04:00.334
HARRY:
Hey, guys.

04:02.409 --> 04:04.434
- Are you okay?
DAN: Oh, yes, sir. Fine.

04:04.611 --> 04:08.673
Considering we're being presided over
by Bucky the Wonder Lump.

04:10.283 --> 04:12.752
Radio City Music Hall called.

04:12.919 --> 04:16.480
The cops just broke up
a Rockettes performance.

04:16.656 --> 04:19.421
We nabbed the whole bunch at once.

04:19.959 --> 04:21.485
You seem happy.

04:21.661 --> 04:24.494
They rejected me in '43.

04:25.732 --> 04:29.327
You tell me,
what's wrong with these gams?

04:34.975 --> 04:38.172
Their loss is clearly our gain.

04:38.945 --> 04:41.209
Sir, this courtroom
is totally out of control.

04:41.381 --> 04:42.405
Yeah, it's funny.

04:42.582 --> 04:46.075
- I never saw the judge act this way before.
- You know this man?

04:46.253 --> 04:48.779
He worked in the Brooklyn courts
when I started there.

04:48.955 --> 04:50.445
Everybody always loved him.

04:50.624 --> 04:53.184
He was fair, he was bright,
he was honest.

04:53.894 --> 04:56.556
And now he's putting hookers' wigs
on Bull.

05:00.967 --> 05:04.767
I'm sorry, son.
but the glare was killing me.

05:10.977 --> 05:12.775
I understand.

05:16.283 --> 05:18.547
[MOUTHS]
<i>Help</i> me.

05:19.686 --> 05:21.745
Sir, you've got to do something.

05:21.922 --> 05:23.321
It's his court, Miss Sullivan.

05:23.490 --> 05:26.118
All I can do is document strange behavior,
make a list...

05:26.293 --> 05:28.284
...and send it
to the judicial review board.

05:28.461 --> 05:29.986
[HORN BLARING]

05:33.033 --> 05:36.833
If I were you, I'd send a copy along
to the Coast Guard while you were at it.

05:37.404 --> 05:39.998
Would counsel approach the bench,
please?

05:41.775 --> 05:45.734
You know why the criminal justice system
isn't working, Mr. Fielding?

05:45.912 --> 05:47.505
Yes, sir.

05:47.781 --> 05:50.478
I mean, not really.

05:50.884 --> 05:53.353
No music in the courtroom.

05:53.520 --> 05:56.922
That's what makes
the whole damn process so dreary.

05:57.090 --> 05:59.889
Imagine how much brighter
this place would be...

06:00.060 --> 06:04.691
...if we piped in Mozart sonatas
or even a few show tunes.

06:05.465 --> 06:09.265
That is a wonderful idea, sir.

06:09.536 --> 06:14.531
You are a sneaky little pile of tweed,
aren't you, boy?

06:15.375 --> 06:16.900
Yes, sir.

06:17.077 --> 06:18.272
HIRSCH:
Take him away.

06:20.714 --> 06:23.877
I knew it. Ha-ha-ha. As soon
as I saw that little smile cracking...

06:24.050 --> 06:27.884
...I could tell the instant
he started talking to me, I just--

06:28.054 --> 06:31.490
You had a visit from your hairy godmother,
didn't you?

06:36.096 --> 06:37.723
- Hi.
HIRSCH: Hi.

06:37.898 --> 06:41.232
- I'm Harry.
- Who the hell cares?

06:41.868 --> 06:44.030
I'm Judge Harry T. Stone.

06:44.804 --> 06:46.966
No. You?

06:47.140 --> 06:48.232
- A judge?
- Uh-huh.

06:48.408 --> 06:52.208
- Your Honor--
- Oh, let's skip the formalities.

06:52.379 --> 06:56.077
It's Bob and Harry,
just like the good old days.

06:56.750 --> 06:58.946
Bob, we don't have any good old days.

06:59.119 --> 07:00.143
We just met.

07:00.320 --> 07:03.221
Oh, what's this Bob garbage then?

07:04.457 --> 07:07.119
I would like to speak to you in private.
In your chambers.

07:07.294 --> 07:08.853
Oh, there's no need.

07:09.029 --> 07:11.657
I have no secrets from these people.

07:11.831 --> 07:14.129
I really do think this would be better
in private.

07:14.301 --> 07:15.325
Nonsense, Harry.

07:15.502 --> 07:21.134
There is nothing that you could say to me
that you can't say before my friends.

07:21.308 --> 07:23.003
What's on your mind?

07:24.945 --> 07:26.538
Sir...

07:31.284 --> 07:33.776
...you're a very sick man.

07:37.891 --> 07:40.121
Company.

07:40.994 --> 07:43.088
[IN NEW YORK ACCENT]
Welcome to the Rock, boss.

07:43.263 --> 07:44.992
Not you too, sir.

07:45.165 --> 07:47.395
Afraid so. No, no. Never mind.

07:47.567 --> 07:49.092
HARRY:
Here you go.

07:56.543 --> 07:59.035
<i>Thank you, Nam Dame“.</i>

08:04.751 --> 08:05.946
You guys okay?

08:06.119 --> 08:08.110
Oh, yes.
Actually, it's very nice down here.

08:08.288 --> 08:12.225
I understand <i>we've</i> made it just in time
for the annual winter mucus test.

08:17.030 --> 08:18.054
Let me guess.

08:18.231 --> 08:19.494
[SNIFFS]

08:19.666 --> 08:21.691
English Leather.

08:24.337 --> 08:25.429
I'm Dan Fielding.

08:25.605 --> 08:27.903
I just killed my family.

08:30.510 --> 08:32.239
Really?

08:32.611 --> 08:34.842
Small world.

08:51.965 --> 08:53.956
[LEEK LAUGHS]

08:55.835 --> 08:58.998
They don't know this
but I really did pull off the job.

08:59.472 --> 09:02.237
I hid the money. Ha, ha.
And they got no witnesses...

09:02.409 --> 09:06.471
...because the guy who saw me without
my mask on is half-blind. Ha-ha-ha.

09:06.646 --> 09:10.674
I hid the getaway car
in a swamp in Jersey. Ha-ha-ha.

09:10.850 --> 09:13.911
I'm gonna getaway with it. Ha-ha-ha.

09:15.955 --> 09:19.516
Two days, I'm gonna be swimming
in cold, hard cash.

09:19.692 --> 09:21.683
[LAUGHING]

09:26.699 --> 09:28.428
So, what's your story?

09:28.601 --> 09:30.729
I'm ajudge.

09:34.874 --> 09:37.138
Dan, you look in.

09:38.912 --> 09:41.347
I gotta go to the bathroom.

09:44.584 --> 09:46.450
TRAUT:
It's over here.

09:52.325 --> 09:53.850
I'd rather...

09:54.027 --> 09:56.325
...explode.

09:57.564 --> 09:58.895
- Hi, guys.
DAN: Hi.

09:59.065 --> 10:00.863
Miss Sullivan, what's going on?

10:01.034 --> 10:02.468
Oh, sir, it's chaos.

10:02.635 --> 10:05.195
I put in an emergency call
to my legal-aid supervisor.

10:05.371 --> 10:09.137
I managed to juggle the docket
so there's only first-time misdemeanors...

10:09.309 --> 10:12.142
...and there's a man in back
wearing the same dress as I am.

10:15.115 --> 10:16.139
What"?

10:16.316 --> 10:17.715
What did you pay for yours?

10:20.987 --> 10:23.456
[PRISONERS WHOOP]

10:30.697 --> 10:32.791
- Any news, Bull?
- Yes.

10:32.966 --> 10:35.833
He just appointed Flo
legal-aid attorney.

10:36.269 --> 10:37.532
He did what?

10:37.704 --> 10:38.933
Bull, let me out of here.

10:42.075 --> 10:44.737
Uh... Listen...

10:44.911 --> 10:48.541
...about that cologne business, I don't
want you to get the wrong impression.

10:48.715 --> 10:51.912
I mean, so many people think
that just because a man wears a dress...

10:52.085 --> 10:53.109
...he's a homosexual.

10:54.087 --> 10:56.181
No.

10:56.689 --> 10:58.919
HARRY:
Okay, guys, let's go, huh?

10:59.792 --> 11:01.157
Hey, wait. Wait, wait, wait.

11:01.327 --> 11:04.888
If Flo is defending, who's prosecuting?

11:05.965 --> 11:11.199
Your Honor, the people feel
the defense's arguments...

11:11.371 --> 11:14.966
...are constructed
on a flimsy legal foundation.

11:16.943 --> 11:19.776
Surely my esteemed colleague
knows the difference...

11:19.946 --> 11:24.042
...between entrapment
and legitimate enforcement of the law.

11:24.217 --> 11:28.176
If not, then I would be so bold
as to question he! abilities...

11:28.354 --> 11:30.618
...to practice in a hall of justice.

11:30.790 --> 11:32.155
Defense?

11:32.325 --> 11:36.819
You're gonna listen to a man
with a dead pigeon in his pocket?

11:38.898 --> 11:40.297
Unbelievable.

11:40.466 --> 11:42.594
Phil's prosecuting?

11:42.769 --> 11:46.399
I've been replaced by a man
who lives in a refrigerator.

11:47.373 --> 11:50.104
Hey, any of you people like
The Three Stooges?

11:51.344 --> 11:57.283
And my favorite one is when Moe is playing
a judge and he says:

11:57.450 --> 12:00.476
“Order, order, order in the courtroom.“

12:00.653 --> 12:03.350
And Curly gets up and says:

12:03.523 --> 12:07.255
“I'll have a ham and cheese on rye.“
Ha, ha.

12:09.596 --> 12:10.620
Judge Hirsch.

12:10.797 --> 12:16.099
Hi there. Wait a minute,
I thought I cited you for contempt.

12:16.269 --> 12:18.636
And how did they get out of jail?

12:18.805 --> 12:21.797
Sir, I cannot tell a lie.

12:21.975 --> 12:23.238
They escaped.

12:25.511 --> 12:26.774
Escaped?

12:26.946 --> 12:28.277
That...

12:28.448 --> 12:29.973
...is not a bad idea.

12:30.149 --> 12:32.584
The whole prison system's overcrowded
anyway.

12:32.752 --> 12:36.382
Guard, go down
and release all the prisoners.

12:37.657 --> 12:39.125
CHRISTINE:
Hold it!

12:39.292 --> 12:41.090
Sir, I'm sorry. You can't do that.

12:41.261 --> 12:43.923
Some of those people are guilty
and have to be dealt with.

12:44.097 --> 12:46.088
You're right, Miss Sullivan.

12:46.266 --> 12:50.635
Tell them they can go but only
it they promise, on their word of honor...

12:50.803 --> 12:53.704
...that they'll go across the street
and clean up that park.

12:54.974 --> 12:57.739
Your Honor,
please step down from the bench.

12:58.278 --> 13:01.407
Bet you my gavel is bigger than yours.

13:02.015 --> 13:04.507
You're in trouble here.
I'd really like to help you.

13:04.684 --> 13:07.312
Me? Need help? That's a lie!

13:07.487 --> 13:10.320
<i>Liar, liar, pants on fire.</i>

13:10.490 --> 13:11.548
It's the truth.

13:11.724 --> 13:12.919
The truth?

13:13.092 --> 13:17.996
This is a court of law, Judge Stone,
this is not a place for truth.

13:18.164 --> 13:20.633
This is a place for lies.

13:20.800 --> 13:23.098
Everybody who comes here lies.

13:23.269 --> 13:28.207
The plaintiffs lie, the defendants lie,
the lawyers lie, the cops Iie.

13:28.374 --> 13:29.569
Everybody lies.

13:29.742 --> 13:32.871
And you expect me
to sift through all this...

13:33.046 --> 13:36.846
...and extract the truth
from all that rubble.

13:37.917 --> 13:40.181
That's what we call justice.

13:40.353 --> 13:42.117
Well, there is no justice.

13:42.288 --> 13:44.450
There never was, there never will be.

13:45.825 --> 13:47.156
Order! Order! Order!

13:47.327 --> 13:49.193
Order in the court!

13:50.396 --> 13:52.228
Oh, come on, people.

13:52.398 --> 13:56.858
You're supposed to say,
“Ham and cheese.

13:57.303 --> 14:00.898
Ham and cheese.“

14:11.751 --> 14:14.550
I guess comedy's subjective, huh?

14:17.423 --> 14:19.289
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

14:22.362 --> 14:23.386
Your Honor.

14:23.563 --> 14:26.430
Oh, Judge Stone. Come in, come in.
I wanna show you something.

14:26.599 --> 14:27.623
Watch this.

14:27.800 --> 14:30.826
H00. H00.

14:31.003 --> 14:34.303
- Looks like a big owl, doesn't it?
- Yeah.

14:34.474 --> 14:36.442
I did that one my first night
on the bench.

14:36.609 --> 14:39.704
I think Oliver Wendell Holmes invented it.

14:39.879 --> 14:41.870
Oh, where's my hospitality?

14:42.048 --> 14:44.278
Come, sit down. Sit down. Sit down.
Ahem.

14:44.917 --> 14:47.477
Uh, aspirin?

14:48.488 --> 14:49.717
No.

14:49.889 --> 14:55.658
You know, most people can't take this
without water.

14:57.597 --> 15:00.089
Your Honor, how long has all this
been going on?

15:00.266 --> 15:02.792
How long has what been going on?

15:02.969 --> 15:07.736
The wigs and the horns and the subscription
to WrestleMania magazine.

15:09.609 --> 15:13.307
You know, Judge Hirsch, I am considered
a bit of a maverick around here myself.

15:13.579 --> 15:16.708
Yeah, word in the halls is you're a flake.

15:17.550 --> 15:19.382
I have my moments.

15:19.552 --> 15:23.420
The point is that I use the gags
and the tricks as a release.

15:23.589 --> 15:26.388
It's to ease the tension, that's all.

15:26.559 --> 15:31.793
It's when it gets taken to an extreme,
when it begins to obstruct justice...

15:31.964 --> 15:37.130
...then it threatens to dismantle
our entire judicial system.

15:39.505 --> 15:41.234
What's your point?

15:43.342 --> 15:46.607
If you don't step down,
I am personally going to file a petition...

15:46.779 --> 15:49.680
...requesting that you be removed
from the bench.

15:52.785 --> 15:57.279
So it comes down to a gunfight, eh?

15:57.457 --> 15:58.982
If need be.

15:59.258 --> 16:00.282
Who draws first?

16:00.460 --> 16:04.727
That usually determines
who wins in these things, right?

16:14.907 --> 16:17.376
Can I, uh, be of some help?

16:17.543 --> 16:19.773
Where the hell is the Corsetti file?

16:20.680 --> 16:23.047
I lined my shoes with it.

16:25.418 --> 16:26.442
You did what?

16:26.619 --> 16:30.556
I didn't think you'd need it anymore.
We finished with the case hours ago.

16:30.723 --> 16:32.122
Finished? How?

16:32.291 --> 16:34.055
Well, the cop's testimony was shaky...

16:34.227 --> 16:37.197
...so I plea-bargained down
to burglary, third degree.

16:37.363 --> 16:39.832
Comes up before grand jury Wednesday.

16:39.999 --> 16:43.560
Oh, God. Wednesdays, I give my blood.

16:45.271 --> 16:47.239
Don't worry. I'll follow through for you.

16:47.406 --> 16:48.464
What a pal.

16:48.641 --> 16:51.440
Don't touch me. I'm not your pal!

16:51.611 --> 16:55.479
You are a disgusting, filthy.
slimy shell 01a human being...

16:55.648 --> 16:59.516
...and you ought to crawl back
into the sewer from which you slithered.

17:00.887 --> 17:03.982
I got a 97 percent conviction rate.

17:05.358 --> 17:09.352
I hear you're batting about 500.

17:13.699 --> 17:15.758
HIRSCH: Wait. What's the matter?
Where are you going?

17:16.035 --> 17:17.502
We haven't finished.

17:17.670 --> 17:19.729
You are finished, Judge Hirsch.

17:19.906 --> 17:21.874
I'm gonna go call for an ambulance.

17:22.040 --> 17:24.703
An ambulance? Are you sick?

17:25.778 --> 17:26.939
I'll be right back.

17:27.213 --> 17:30.649
- You wanna hear a funny story, Harry?
- Your Honor--

17:30.816 --> 17:36.983
There was this girl, 17, beautiful girl,
dark complexion, dark hair...

17:37.156 --> 17:41.354
...and a welt under her eye
where her husband had hither.

17:42.995 --> 17:45.123
She was pregnant for the third time,
I think.

17:45.298 --> 17:49.633
And the DA said they lived in
a rat-infested place on the Lower East Side.

17:49.802 --> 17:52.635
She said she wanted her husband
to stop hitting her.

17:52.805 --> 17:55.137
As soon as I indicated
that I'd send him to jail...

17:55.308 --> 17:59.211
...zip, she changed her testimony,
said she was lying.

17:59.378 --> 18:01.506
She didn't want her husband
to go to jail.

18:01.681 --> 18:04.309
He brought home money
so the family can eat.

18:04.483 --> 18:07.885
All she wanted was for him
to stop hitting her!

18:08.054 --> 18:11.080
Well, Harry, I can't make him stop!

18:11.257 --> 18:16.127
In 25 years,
I've never made anybody stop!

18:22.501 --> 18:23.832
I'm sorry.

18:25.504 --> 18:26.903
God's in his heaven...

18:27.073 --> 18:32.534
...but all's not quite right in the world.

18:34.547 --> 18:36.208
I know how you feel.

18:36.682 --> 18:38.411
How long have you been on the bench?

18:38.818 --> 18:39.842
Three years.

18:40.019 --> 18:42.386
Ha-ha-ha. Three years.

18:42.555 --> 18:46.856
I've had bouts of irregularity
longer than that.

18:49.895 --> 18:50.919
[SIGHS]

18:51.097 --> 18:54.465
My God, what have I done?

18:55.334 --> 18:56.995
How much do you remember?

18:57.203 --> 19:01.800
Uh, coloring a little piggy...

19:01.974 --> 19:05.740
...and a monster with a blond wig.

19:08.080 --> 19:09.912
Am I sick, Harry?

19:10.616 --> 19:12.516
Maybe a little.

19:12.985 --> 19:14.817
But mostly...

19:15.488 --> 19:17.513
...I'd say you're real, real tired.

19:17.690 --> 19:18.885
Oh, tired.

19:19.058 --> 19:24.360
Oh, I could sleep for a million years.
Ha, ha.

19:24.630 --> 19:25.961
Yeah.

19:26.132 --> 19:31.593
If the bed they strap me down to
is comfortable, I probably will.

19:33.372 --> 19:37.206
See, I tried to do it all right.

19:37.376 --> 19:40.573
I tried to right all the wrongs...

19:40.746 --> 19:44.478
...reverse all of the injustices.

19:44.650 --> 19:47.142
I guess I was wrong.

19:47.319 --> 19:48.514
It's impossible.

19:49.455 --> 19:52.914
Even a tool knows that we can't reach out
and touch the stars...

19:53.092 --> 19:56.289
...but that does not stop
the wise man from trying.

19:57.430 --> 19:59.330
I like that.

19:59.832 --> 20:01.061
Who said that?

20:01.233 --> 20:02.667
You did.

20:02.835 --> 20:05.463
It was in a speech to the bar association.

20:07.473 --> 20:08.998
Here.

20:14.180 --> 20:16.615
You can never have...

20:16.782 --> 20:18.546
...too many.

20:19.885 --> 20:21.444
I'll wear it with honor, sir.

20:21.787 --> 20:23.721
You do that.

20:24.256 --> 20:26.281
I gotta go.

20:26.659 --> 20:31.096
Somewhere there's an inkblot
with my name on it.

20:32.231 --> 20:33.892
[SIGHS]

